cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict semantic similarity between short texts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a transfer learning approach based on LSTM, which is a popular deep learning technique used in various fields, including natural language processing. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with multi-task learning and regression, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses neural networks to make predictions, which is a common technique in neural engineering (cs.NE).
